WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.741 --> 00:00:14.101
Nancy.
Bohlale was asked the following question.

2
00:00:14.821 --> 00:00:17.101
"Did you have sex with Mia?"

3
00:00:19.941 --> 00:00:21.341
This is how he answered.

4
00:00:25.781 --> 00:00:26.661
Yes.

5
00:00:29.821 --> 00:00:30.981
And that answer is…

6
00:00:33.021 --> 00:00:34.141
[voice] Truth.

7
00:00:37.780 --> 00:00:39.261
I feel stupid.

8
00:00:44.821 --> 00:00:46.141
[in Zulu] Bohlale doesn't deserve me.

9
00:00:47.101 --> 00:00:49.261
I won't forgive him
for the rest of my life.

10
00:00:49.341 --> 00:00:50.981
[in English] That's very fair.

11
00:00:51.061 --> 00:00:55.181
[in Zulu] Because he humiliated me
for the rest of my life.

12
00:00:57.221 --> 00:01:01.861
[in English] Bohlale's honesty
added 10.000 rand to the prize pot.

13
00:01:02.581 --> 00:01:04.861
Thank you. Nancy.
You can return to your seat.

14
00:01:06.501 --> 00:01:08.661
[Nancy. in Zulu]
What you have done has shattered my heart.

15
00:01:08.741 --> 00:01:10.101
It has broken my spirit.

16
00:01:10.181 --> 00:01:12.621
[in English]
I'm so disappointed. Yoh. [exhales]

17
00:01:13.901 --> 00:01:15.141
[Nancy sniffles]

18
00:01:20.061 --> 00:01:22.221
Nikiwe. it's your turn.

19
00:01:25.061 --> 00:01:25.981
[exhales]

20
00:01:26.061 --> 00:01:28.901
You've been looking very stressed out.

21
00:01:28.981 --> 00:01:31.101
One thing about my face.
it never tells lies.

22
00:01:31.181 --> 00:01:32.421
No. it does not.

23
00:01:32.501 --> 00:01:34.421
It's clearly not that hard

24
00:01:34.501 --> 00:01:40.221
to lose sight of the commitment you made
to someone else in 2.5 seconds.

25
00:01:40.861 --> 00:01:43.341
Please take a look at this clip.

26
00:01:43.421 --> 00:01:44.821
[exhales]

27
00:01:45.541 --> 00:01:46.861
[Naledi] I said this to her very recently.

28
00:01:46.941 --> 00:01:48.101
I'm like. "Dawg. I don't care

29
00:01:48.181 --> 00:01:49.381
-about your money…
-[Wilfred] Mm-hmm.

30
00:01:49.461 --> 00:01:51.701
…but I care about you having it
when you have it."

31
00:01:51.781 --> 00:01:53.821
-[Wilfred] Exactly.
-"And what are you doing with it?"

32
00:01:53.901 --> 00:01:55.701
-Yeah.
-"Why do you not have…"

33
00:01:55.781 --> 00:01:59.341
You need to be able to buy yourself
a pair of shoes every month.

34
00:01:59.421 --> 00:02:01.741
Right? To take your kid on a fucking trip.

35
00:02:01.821 --> 00:02:04.021
and he must buy
whatever the heck he wants.

36
00:02:04.101 --> 00:02:05.981
-[Wilfred] Yeah.
-Why can't you do that?

37
00:02:06.061 --> 00:02:09.501
That's a big… Like.
the financial part is a huge problem.

38
00:02:11.221 --> 00:02:13.261
Are these concerns you've heard before?

39
00:02:13.341 --> 00:02:15.301
These are concerns I've heard before.

40
00:02:15.381 --> 00:02:17.701
I'm particularly pissed off

41
00:02:17.781 --> 00:02:23.341
because I don't feel comfortable with you
discussing my money situations

42
00:02:23.421 --> 00:02:25.741
and what I can and cannot do for my kid.

43
00:02:26.301 --> 00:02:29.461
I think somebody got lost in the sauce.

44
00:02:29.541 --> 00:02:33.021
and forgot that there are just certain
things you don't hold with your mouth

45
00:02:33.541 --> 00:02:34.981
when I'm not around.

46
00:02:36.101 --> 00:02:37.501
What are your deal-breakers. Nikiwe?

47
00:02:37.581 --> 00:02:38.821
My kid!

48
00:02:39.701 --> 00:02:41.581
Why is my kid an example?

49
00:02:41.661 --> 00:02:44.781
Why do you think you can say
stuff like this to other people?

50
00:02:44.861 --> 00:02:46.341
You don't know these people.

51
00:02:46.421 --> 00:02:48.821
I don't trust them like I trust you.

52
00:02:48.901 --> 00:02:50.101
What are you doing?

53
00:02:50.181 --> 00:02:51.181
What are you on?

54
00:02:53.541 --> 00:02:56.901
Nikiwe. your partner received
the following question.

55
00:02:57.501 --> 00:03:01.901
"Do you resent the fact that
you are financially dependent on Nikiwe?"

56
00:03:02.941 --> 00:03:04.701
This is how they answered.

57
00:03:08.301 --> 00:03:09.261
No.

58
00:03:10.501 --> 00:03:11.781
And that answer is…

59
00:03:14.301 --> 00:03:15.301
[voice] Truth.

60
00:03:18.621 --> 00:03:20.101
That's very interesting.

61
00:03:20.181 --> 00:03:23.061
I am intensely disappointed. [sniffles]

62
00:03:23.141 --> 00:03:26.261
That moment. for me.
was someone I didn't recognize.

63
00:03:27.101 --> 00:03:30.261
That was someone who would tell anyone
anything about me.

64
00:03:30.341 --> 00:03:32.341
and I don't know if I feel safe.

65
00:03:35.421 --> 00:03:39.381
Naledi's honesty
added 10.000 rand to the prize pot.

66
00:03:40.421 --> 00:03:43.221
Nikiwe. I'd like you
to watch another clip.

67
00:03:44.941 --> 00:03:46.941
[Wilfred]
What would you do if she tells you. like.

68
00:03:47.021 --> 00:03:49.381
-she wants to be monogamous?
-Yoh! [chuckles]

69
00:03:49.461 --> 00:03:50.701
"Yoh!" That's what I'd do.

70
00:03:50.781 --> 00:03:52.421
-I know I'm polyamorous. right?
-[chuckles]

71
00:03:52.501 --> 00:03:53.821
I know right now I…

72
00:03:53.901 --> 00:03:55.101
I just wanna be with her.

73
00:03:55.181 --> 00:03:59.661
but I know. like…
I can almost hear monogamous settling in.

74
00:03:59.741 --> 00:04:01.021
-Mm-hmm.
-And I'm like…

75
00:04:01.101 --> 00:04:02.221
-Mm-mmm.
-Hmm.

76
00:04:02.301 --> 00:04:05.901
I think. in the depths of my spirit.
I'm. like. very flowy.

77
00:04:05.981 --> 00:04:07.701
So. like. you're reminding me of that.
like…

78
00:04:07.781 --> 00:04:09.101
-Mm-hmm.
-…a lot--

79
00:04:09.181 --> 00:04:12.621
-I remind you of yourself.
-A lot more than I'd like to feel.

80
00:04:12.701 --> 00:04:14.181
-Like…
-[Imogel laughs]

81
00:04:16.301 --> 00:04:17.821
How did that make you feel?

82
00:04:18.861 --> 00:04:23.661
I'm thinking about the fact that
that person is chatting about polyamory

83
00:04:23.741 --> 00:04:26.181
like they didn't ask me
to stop seeing people.

84
00:04:26.701 --> 00:04:28.941
That person is not polyamorous.

85
00:04:29.021 --> 00:04:31.061
They're polygamous.

86
00:04:31.141 --> 00:04:33.981
Because they want more than one partner.

87
00:04:34.061 --> 00:04:35.821
but did not want me
to have another partner.

88
00:04:35.901 --> 00:04:37.581
That's crazy to me.

89
00:04:39.621 --> 00:04:40.741
I don't know that guy.

90
00:04:43.541 --> 00:04:44.541
Nikiwe.

91
00:04:45.581 --> 00:04:48.621
Your partner was asked
the following question.

92
00:04:49.181 --> 00:04:52.341
"Do you want to be
exclusively monogamous with Nikiwe?"

93
00:04:53.421 --> 00:04:54.501
And they answered…

94
00:04:58.701 --> 00:04:59.741
No.

95
00:05:00.981 --> 00:05:02.821
And that answer is…

96
00:05:05.701 --> 00:05:07.141
[voice] Lie.

97
00:05:07.861 --> 00:05:10.541
[laughing]

98
00:05:13.621 --> 00:05:14.741
I'm sorry.

99
00:05:15.621 --> 00:05:18.381
I am very okay with being monogamous.

100
00:05:18.981 --> 00:05:20.701
They're not ready to let that go.

101
00:05:21.901 --> 00:05:25.541
The two of you talk a lot
about the fact that you're engaged.

102
00:05:26.141 --> 00:05:29.021
Do you think
you are both ready for that next step?

103
00:05:29.101 --> 00:05:30.741
I think I am ready for that next step.

104
00:05:31.541 --> 00:05:35.501
And I think maybe it's because
a part of me is. like. really hoping.

105
00:05:35.581 --> 00:05:38.461
like… [sobbing] …maybe that shit
was taken out of context

106
00:05:38.541 --> 00:05:40.861
and you didn't mean to mention
my kid and my shit.

107
00:05:40.941 --> 00:05:44.341
and. like. you didn't…
Like. you didn't mean to do me like that.

108
00:05:44.941 --> 00:05:48.181
Like I'm hoping…
Like. there's a part of me hoping. like…

109
00:05:54.781 --> 00:05:57.261
Nikiwe. you have a lot to reflect on.

110
00:05:58.461 --> 00:06:02.021
Naledi's lie took away 10.000 rand
from your prize pot.

111
00:06:03.421 --> 00:06:04.501
Thank you. Nikiwe.

112
00:06:04.581 --> 00:06:06.101
You may take your seat.

113
00:06:08.261 --> 00:06:10.221
Gontse. please join me.

114
00:06:10.301 --> 00:06:11.301
[Gontse sighs]

115
00:06:14.661 --> 00:06:16.101
Are you worried about tonight?

116
00:06:16.181 --> 00:06:18.621
I'm worried that. you know.
she might not consider me

117
00:06:18.701 --> 00:06:21.621
with her actions and everything. so yeah.

118
00:06:22.661 --> 00:06:24.341
I'd like you to watch the next clip.

119
00:06:28.141 --> 00:06:30.781
Me and Jordan's spark has like…
It's grown.

120
00:06:30.861 --> 00:06:32.701
I feel safer. I feel more comfortable.

121
00:06:32.781 --> 00:06:34.901
I'm starting to like him.

122
00:06:34.981 --> 00:06:37.381
We have something that can grow into more.

123
00:06:37.461 --> 00:06:41.101
If there's one thing. I feel like.
I really appreciate about you.

124
00:06:41.181 --> 00:06:42.661
is that. like. you're a man.

125
00:06:43.261 --> 00:06:44.861
I wanna feel secure in my relationship.

126
00:06:44.941 --> 00:06:46.861
I wanna feel safe. I wanna feel trust.

127
00:06:46.941 --> 00:06:48.341
but I don't know if I have that.

128
00:06:48.421 --> 00:06:49.981
One thing I really like about you

129
00:06:50.061 --> 00:06:54.901
is we can be calm and serious
and have honest conversations.

130
00:06:54.981 --> 00:06:56.621
Jordan creates a safe space for me

131
00:06:56.701 --> 00:06:59.661
to express my feelings
and to be vulnerable.

132
00:07:00.181 --> 00:07:02.541
and I don't feel that with my partner.

133
00:07:05.981 --> 00:07:07.181
What do you think?

134
00:07:07.261 --> 00:07:11.581
It's clearly. you know. you've just
wanted something else the whole time.

135
00:07:11.661 --> 00:07:14.221
There's certain aspects
that I can grow as a person.

136
00:07:14.301 --> 00:07:16.541
but there's certain things
that I'll always be.

137
00:07:16.621 --> 00:07:19.061
And I can only grow and change so much

138
00:07:19.141 --> 00:07:21.981
till the point that
she just wants a different person.

139
00:07:22.061 --> 00:07:25.541
Well. she said that you're not serious.

140
00:07:25.621 --> 00:07:27.621
You like to joke around all the time.

141
00:07:27.701 --> 00:07:31.821
Is that something you're willing
to work on. or is that just how you are?

142
00:07:31.901 --> 00:07:35.101
I would say there are times
where I take it a bit overboard.

143
00:07:35.181 --> 00:07:36.581
I do hear her concerns.

144
00:07:36.661 --> 00:07:40.261
but clearly it doesn't matter whether
I hear them or not anymore. you know.

145
00:07:40.781 --> 00:07:44.461
Gontse. your partner was asked
the following question.

146
00:07:45.061 --> 00:07:48.941
"Is it easier to be vulnerable with Jordan
than it is with Gontse?"

147
00:07:50.941 --> 00:07:52.181
This is how she answered.

148
00:07:56.221 --> 00:07:57.181
Yes.

149
00:07:58.741 --> 00:08:00.221
And that answer is…

150
00:08:02.901 --> 00:08:04.061
[voice] Truth.

151
00:08:06.661 --> 00:08:07.581
[whispers] It's okay.

152
00:08:08.621 --> 00:08:11.341
Are you emotionally closed off maybe?

153
00:08:11.861 --> 00:08:13.341
I would say yes. I am.

154
00:08:13.421 --> 00:08:18.941
but I've also felt. in more recent times
with Munaka. it's become more extreme.

155
00:08:19.021 --> 00:08:22.381
I'm still open to seeing everything.
you know. uh…

156
00:08:22.461 --> 00:08:24.301
Working on the relationship.

157
00:08:25.341 --> 00:08:27.661
So. I'm just gonna take everything
as it comes.

158
00:08:29.901 --> 00:08:33.741
Munaka's honesty added 10.000 rand
to the prize pot.

159
00:08:33.821 --> 00:08:36.181
Gontse. I have another clip for you.

160
00:08:38.421 --> 00:08:40.621
If I don't resolve the issues
that I came here to resolve.

161
00:08:40.700 --> 00:08:42.301
like. I'm not gonna leave with him.

162
00:08:42.381 --> 00:08:44.101
Like. I'm gonna have to do
what's right for me.

163
00:08:44.180 --> 00:08:45.901
-[Mia] Yeah.
-And…

164
00:08:45.981 --> 00:08:46.981
My feelings are valid.

165
00:08:47.060 --> 00:08:49.461
I should not feel bad
for wanting certain things.

166
00:08:49.541 --> 00:08:50.741
-You know him?
-Gontse. Gontse?

167
00:08:50.821 --> 00:08:52.061
Yeah. that's my boyfriend.

168
00:08:52.141 --> 00:08:53.141
Goddamn it.

169
00:08:54.021 --> 00:08:55.221
We went out on a date.

170
00:08:55.301 --> 00:08:57.581
-You and Gontse went… When was this?
-Yeah. it was like last year.

171
00:08:57.661 --> 00:08:59.381
One thing I can tell you for a fact.

172
00:08:59.461 --> 00:09:01.421
-he is very selfish.
-Yeah.

173
00:09:02.461 --> 00:09:05.701
I would really say.
in this situation. put yourself first.

174
00:09:06.221 --> 00:09:08.061
-Are you in love with him?
-No.

175
00:09:08.141 --> 00:09:09.781
-There you go. Done.
-Yeah.

176
00:09:09.861 --> 00:09:11.221
What else do you need to know?

177
00:09:14.901 --> 00:09:16.421
[in Zulu] Let's start with the date.

178
00:09:16.501 --> 00:09:18.301
[Gontse. in English] Eish. eish. you know?

179
00:09:18.381 --> 00:09:19.781
Yeah. I do know Mallay.

180
00:09:19.861 --> 00:09:21.221
I have taken her out on a date.

181
00:09:21.301 --> 00:09:22.621
That was also a while ago.

182
00:09:23.221 --> 00:09:26.981
How did you feel about
what Mallay was saying about you though.

183
00:09:27.061 --> 00:09:29.981
and the fact that Munaka was agreeing?

184
00:09:30.061 --> 00:09:30.941
That I'm selfish?

185
00:09:31.021 --> 00:09:33.381
Maybe when I first met Mo.
I was still that person.

186
00:09:33.461 --> 00:09:35.381
but over time. I've grown out of that.

187
00:09:35.461 --> 00:09:38.381
I can't. forever. for the rest of my life.
be paying for the sins

188
00:09:38.461 --> 00:09:39.661
of who I used to be.

189
00:09:39.741 --> 00:09:42.861
And her saying. when they asked her
does she love me…

190
00:09:42.941 --> 00:09:45.261
I'm always the one that's hesitant
to say it. but you're always…

191
00:09:45.341 --> 00:09:47.421
you're the first one to say.
"Aw. Gontse. I love you. Say it back."

192
00:09:47.501 --> 00:09:49.901
Clearly. I don't know
who I've been with this whole time.

193
00:09:50.821 --> 00:09:53.461
Gontse. Munaka was asked
the following question.

194
00:09:54.341 --> 00:09:56.221
"Are you in love with Gontse?"

195
00:09:58.541 --> 00:10:00.021
This is how she answered.

196
00:10:04.981 --> 00:10:05.901
No.

197
00:10:07.661 --> 00:10:09.141
And that answer is…

198
00:10:12.021 --> 00:10:13.541
[voice] Lie.

199
00:10:16.661 --> 00:10:18.941
It really doesn't make a difference. hey?

200
00:10:19.021 --> 00:10:21.861
Because if you can get lost in the moment.

201
00:10:21.941 --> 00:10:24.941
as soon as people are around.
you're like. "Ugh. nah. I don't love him."

202
00:10:25.021 --> 00:10:27.861
The whole bandwagon is saying.
"Ah. nah. Say you don't."

203
00:10:27.941 --> 00:10:28.861
So. maybe it's that.

204
00:10:28.941 --> 00:10:30.021
I don't know.

205
00:10:30.781 --> 00:10:36.101
Munaka's lie took away 10.000 rand
from the prize pot.

206
00:10:36.701 --> 00:10:39.021
Thank you. Gontse.
You can return to your seat.

207
00:10:51.541 --> 00:10:53.221
Kuda. please join me.

208
00:10:56.981 --> 00:10:58.221
How are you feeling about tonight?

209
00:10:59.261 --> 00:11:02.581
The last time I was in this seat.
it was a bit of a movie.

210
00:11:03.621 --> 00:11:05.501
So. not my favorite place. you know?

211
00:11:06.621 --> 00:11:07.661
You ready. Kuda?

212
00:11:08.781 --> 00:11:10.541
I'd like you to please watch this clip.

213
00:11:11.541 --> 00:11:12.741
Today. I'm feeling light. man.

214
00:11:12.821 --> 00:11:16.341
If he thought it was fine to sleep under
the covers with people he doesn't know…

215
00:11:16.421 --> 00:11:18.301
[in Zulu]
Be a bad bitch then. what can one say?

216
00:11:18.381 --> 00:11:21.141
[in English] And I was like.
"Eish. I take my boy's girl."

217
00:11:21.221 --> 00:11:22.381
-Then Siya's--
-That's why!

218
00:11:22.461 --> 00:11:24.301
-[laughs]
-Siya's looking at me like this.

219
00:11:24.381 --> 00:11:27.141
-Am I developing feelings for Lynn?
-[Lynn] Ah.

220
00:11:27.221 --> 00:11:30.221
[Veezo] Yeah. man.
It's giving a relationship feeling.

221
00:11:30.301 --> 00:11:32.581
and it's getting weird.

222
00:11:33.341 --> 00:11:35.421
But weird in a good way.

223
00:11:40.341 --> 00:11:41.821
Is it getting weird?

224
00:11:41.901 --> 00:11:43.501
-It's getting weird.
-[Minnie chuckles]

225
00:11:43.581 --> 00:11:44.981
[in Zulu] It's awkward. Yoh.

226
00:11:45.661 --> 00:11:46.741
No. man.

227
00:11:46.821 --> 00:11:48.301
It sorta hurts.

228
00:11:48.381 --> 00:11:52.021
It's like two single people
getting to know each other.

229
00:11:53.981 --> 00:11:57.861
Kuda. your partner received
the following question.

230
00:11:58.461 --> 00:12:01.381
"Do you have a crush on Veezo?"

231
00:12:04.261 --> 00:12:05.501
Lynn answered…

232
00:12:10.101 --> 00:12:11.061
Yes.

233
00:12:12.421 --> 00:12:14.101
And her answer is…

234
00:12:15.821 --> 00:12:16.861
[voice] Truth.

235
00:12:20.541 --> 00:12:21.541
Happy for her.

236
00:12:22.061 --> 00:12:23.901
You're sounding like you're done.

237
00:12:23.981 --> 00:12:24.821
I'm not done.

238
00:12:24.901 --> 00:12:28.661
The conversation we have.
when we get to finish it off. will…

239
00:12:29.261 --> 00:12:30.421
will tell.

240
00:12:30.501 --> 00:12:31.781
Okay.

241
00:12:32.781 --> 00:12:36.541
Lynn's honesty added 10.000 rand
to the prize pot.

242
00:12:37.581 --> 00:12:40.981
Kuda. I'd like you to watch one more clip.

243
00:12:42.141 --> 00:12:43.621
[Nikiwe exhales]

244
00:12:43.701 --> 00:12:44.781
Tense.

245
00:12:45.381 --> 00:12:47.101
I would like to have a lot more confidence

246
00:12:47.181 --> 00:12:48.181
-in my relationship.
-Mm-mmm.

247
00:12:48.261 --> 00:12:50.661
The fact that I can wear
whatever I wanna wear

248
00:12:50.741 --> 00:12:53.101
without having to nurse

249
00:12:53.181 --> 00:12:55.661
-or think about your insecurities.
-Mm-mmm.

250
00:12:55.741 --> 00:12:57.581
Kuda in the club is bouncing
from wall to wall.

251
00:12:57.661 --> 00:12:59.861
And then. I'm standing there like this.

252
00:13:01.261 --> 00:13:03.621
It's a lot of pressure
having someone to take care of.

253
00:13:03.701 --> 00:13:05.861
We're finally asking the right questions.

254
00:13:05.941 --> 00:13:08.101
and finding introspection
in the right ways.

255
00:13:08.181 --> 00:13:11.381
-Kuda uses logic.
-Mm-mmm.

256
00:13:11.461 --> 00:13:13.461
-But you're not telling me how you feel.
-Exactly.

257
00:13:13.541 --> 00:13:15.061
"I feel frustrated.
Lynn. I'm angry. bruh."

258
00:13:15.141 --> 00:13:16.461
Maybe that's the best thing they ever did

259
00:13:16.541 --> 00:13:17.621
-for us.
-True.

260
00:13:17.701 --> 00:13:20.381
-Was separate us from our people so that…
-Yeah. the separation is helping.

261
00:13:20.461 --> 00:13:23.261
-…we can rediscover our own identity.
-Ourselves. yes.

262
00:13:26.421 --> 00:13:29.461
At least this time.
it's not stuff she hasn't voiced.

263
00:13:29.541 --> 00:13:32.621
I guess she's getting a chance
to vent about it again.

264
00:13:32.701 --> 00:13:35.061
and it's something I've tried to work on.

265
00:13:37.261 --> 00:13:40.221
Kuda. Lynn received
the following question.

266
00:13:40.821 --> 00:13:43.541
"Will you ever be ready to marry Kuda?"

267
00:13:43.621 --> 00:13:44.581
-[mouths word] What?
-[Kuda] Hmm.

268
00:13:45.581 --> 00:13:46.821
This is what she said.

269
00:13:50.381 --> 00:13:51.381
No.

270
00:13:52.821 --> 00:13:54.421
And her answer is…

271
00:13:56.221 --> 00:13:57.821
[voice] Lie.

272
00:13:57.901 --> 00:13:59.101
Oh. my goodness.

273
00:14:00.381 --> 00:14:02.141
-[chuckles]
-My heart.

274
00:14:02.701 --> 00:14:07.301
Uh. maybe. you see.
the experience is giving her that mind-set

275
00:14:07.381 --> 00:14:09.621
that I'm able to start over.

276
00:14:09.701 --> 00:14:10.541
-So…
-Kuda.

277
00:14:10.621 --> 00:14:12.221
It was a lie.

278
00:14:12.301 --> 00:14:14.581
-It was a lie. but--
-Which means?

279
00:14:14.661 --> 00:14:16.261
She was trying to tell the truth.

280
00:14:16.861 --> 00:14:18.141
Okay.

281
00:14:19.181 --> 00:14:24.141
Lynn's lie has taken away 10.000 rand
from the prize pot.

282
00:14:24.701 --> 00:14:26.341
Kuda. you can take your seat.

283
00:14:29.221 --> 00:14:30.061
[Kuda] Yoh.

284
00:14:30.141 --> 00:14:33.381
Lynn is clearly over me.

285
00:14:33.461 --> 00:14:37.101
So I guess I'm the idiot.

286
00:14:42.101 --> 00:14:47.421
I hope that what you all saw
and heard here tonight

287
00:14:47.501 --> 00:14:49.981
gave you the insight that you need.

288
00:14:50.941 --> 00:14:52.141
Thank you. lovelies.

289
00:15:01.141 --> 00:15:03.581
It's so funny
because they were influencing each other

290
00:15:03.661 --> 00:15:04.941
-to do this shit.
-The two of them slept together.

291
00:15:05.021 --> 00:15:06.701
[Kuda] I told you guys. Herd mentality.

292
00:15:06.781 --> 00:15:08.421
Herd mentality is a real thing.

293
00:15:08.501 --> 00:15:09.381
Me. I'm just shocked.

294
00:15:09.461 --> 00:15:12.621
They influenced my partner
into saying they don't love me. Yoh.

295
00:15:12.701 --> 00:15:15.981
And you are venting
to a hun that wants to fuck you.

296
00:15:16.061 --> 00:15:18.341
I will embarrass myself to that point.

297
00:15:18.421 --> 00:15:23.501
And after this relationship.
no one will ever be able to get to me.

298
00:15:23.581 --> 00:15:24.741
It's enough for me now.

299
00:15:24.821 --> 00:15:26.381
-Like this is as much…
-Uh-huh.

300
00:15:26.461 --> 00:15:28.421
This is how much I can handle.

301
00:15:28.501 --> 00:15:30.021
Well. let me comfort you. okay?

302
00:15:30.101 --> 00:15:33.101
I guarantee you
that girl does not want Siya.

303
00:15:33.181 --> 00:15:34.501
[groans]

304
00:15:34.581 --> 00:15:36.461
[in Zulu] You went and humiliated me.

305
00:15:36.541 --> 00:15:39.141
[in English]
I can't do this relationship with you.

306
00:15:39.221 --> 00:15:41.101
Not now. not ever.

307
00:15:41.181 --> 00:15:42.181
[sighs]

308
00:15:55.301 --> 00:15:57.221
I don't feel good. [chuckles]

309
00:15:57.301 --> 00:15:59.941
[sighs] This connection that I established

310
00:16:00.021 --> 00:16:01.661
with a person who was a stranger

311
00:16:01.741 --> 00:16:03.581
brought me closer to myself.

312
00:16:03.661 --> 00:16:06.741
and I was pursuing me.

313
00:16:06.821 --> 00:16:09.501
you know.
rather than thinking about it more.

314
00:16:11.301 --> 00:16:13.941
I'm disappointed in you.
but I'm not angry at you.

315
00:16:14.021 --> 00:16:15.741
Like what you did was a mistake.

316
00:16:15.821 --> 00:16:16.781
It's fine.

317
00:16:16.861 --> 00:16:19.261
But the fact that. at least.
you can acknowledge where you're wrong.

318
00:16:19.341 --> 00:16:21.501
-that's a good start.
-Mm-hmm. [sniffles]

319
00:16:21.581 --> 00:16:22.661
[chuckles]

320
00:16:22.741 --> 00:16:23.781
I'm really…

321
00:16:24.341 --> 00:16:26.661
I'm really afraid of losing Nancy.

322
00:16:26.741 --> 00:16:27.901
Let me put it like that.

323
00:16:41.061 --> 00:16:42.901
[Minnie] Change is in the air.

324
00:16:42.981 --> 00:16:44.821
and those who missed out on all the fun

325
00:16:44.901 --> 00:16:47.941
will now get to live it up
in Villa Umjolo.

326
00:16:48.021 --> 00:16:49.301
Their partners. however…

327
00:16:49.381 --> 00:16:52.501
They now have to deal with
the consequences of their actions.

328
00:16:52.581 --> 00:16:57.061
Shortly. I will show them how
the last Love Never Lies ceremony went.

329
00:17:02.261 --> 00:17:04.941
How is Villa Umgowo treating you?

330
00:17:05.021 --> 00:17:06.861
-We're going through it.
-It's all right.

331
00:17:06.941 --> 00:17:08.501
-But we're still okay. right?
-[participants laugh]

332
00:17:08.581 --> 00:17:10.221
-[Clayton] Yeah.
-[Minnie] Okay.

333
00:17:10.301 --> 00:17:14.340
As you know.
you were all tested by EyeDetect.

334
00:17:14.421 --> 00:17:18.541
Your partners took part in
a Love Never Lies ceremony.

335
00:17:18.620 --> 00:17:21.221
during which they learnt your answers.

336
00:17:21.301 --> 00:17:27.301
Your partners got to see how you all spent
your time in Villa Umjolo.

337
00:17:28.541 --> 00:17:32.461
In a few moments. you will get to see
how they reacted

338
00:17:32.541 --> 00:17:34.621
to what they saw and heard.

339
00:17:34.701 --> 00:17:37.101
These. however. are only fragments.

340
00:17:37.181 --> 00:17:38.821
You will not get to see

341
00:17:38.901 --> 00:17:42.701
whether your answers were
the truth or a lie.

342
00:17:42.781 --> 00:17:44.021
[exhales]

343
00:17:45.261 --> 00:17:46.941
Please proceed to the living room.

344
00:17:47.021 --> 00:17:49.941
You'll be watching your videos one by one.

345
00:17:50.741 --> 00:17:52.461
Lynn. please stay.

346
00:18:00.381 --> 00:18:01.661
-Lynn?
-Yes.

347
00:18:01.741 --> 00:18:04.421
-How are you doing?
-I'm well. thank you. A bit scared now.

348
00:18:04.501 --> 00:18:05.581
I would've loved to be there

349
00:18:05.661 --> 00:18:07.861
to explain
why my answers are the way they are.

350
00:18:07.941 --> 00:18:09.621
-Are you ready?
-I am.

351
00:18:09.701 --> 00:18:11.381
Okay. let's take a look.

352
00:18:11.461 --> 00:18:12.421
Okay.

353
00:18:13.701 --> 00:18:15.581
If he thought it was fine to sleep
under the covers

354
00:18:15.661 --> 00:18:16.901
with people that he doesn't know…

355
00:18:16.981 --> 00:18:19.181
[in Zulu]
Be a bad bitch then. what can one say?

356
00:18:19.261 --> 00:18:21.941
[in English] Maybe that's the best
thing they ever did for us was separate us

357
00:18:22.021 --> 00:18:23.341
-from our people so we can…
-Separation is helping.

358
00:18:23.421 --> 00:18:25.621
-…rediscover our own identity.
-Ourselves. yes.

359
00:18:25.701 --> 00:18:28.421
Will you ever be ready to marry Kuda?

360
00:18:29.021 --> 00:18:30.901
-No.
-[gasps]

361
00:18:30.981 --> 00:18:32.221
[Kuda] I guess it is what it is.

362
00:18:32.301 --> 00:18:35.741
I can't feel worse than I do now. can I?

363
00:18:35.821 --> 00:18:37.661
She said she ain't ready to marry me.

364
00:18:37.741 --> 00:18:40.941
And now she's thinking
I'm not the guy for her.

365
00:18:41.021 --> 00:18:43.461
I guess I'm the idiot.

366
00:18:45.781 --> 00:18:46.781
Oh. my God.

367
00:18:46.861 --> 00:18:48.341
What's going through your mind?

368
00:18:48.421 --> 00:18:51.341
That's not how I wanted to make him feel.

369
00:18:51.941 --> 00:18:53.341
What are you worried about the most?

370
00:18:53.421 --> 00:18:55.901
That he's going to retaliate.
That he thinks I'm over him.

371
00:18:55.981 --> 00:18:58.501
Do you want to marry Kuda?

372
00:18:58.581 --> 00:18:59.781
I do want to marry Kuda.

373
00:18:59.861 --> 00:19:01.701
but I have to marry a different Kuda.

374
00:19:01.781 --> 00:19:03.781
It cannot be the Kuda that I'm with today.

375
00:19:03.861 --> 00:19:05.621
It seems like you've got a lot
to think about.

376
00:19:05.701 --> 00:19:07.341
-Absolutely.
-I'll see you soon.

377
00:19:07.421 --> 00:19:08.341
-Thank you so much.
-Okay.

378
00:19:08.421 --> 00:19:09.581
All right.

379
00:19:09.661 --> 00:19:13.741
It is extremely heartbreaking for me
to see the pain in my boyfriend's eyes.

380
00:19:14.981 --> 00:19:16.101
Oh. my God.

381
00:19:16.181 --> 00:19:17.901
-[Naledi] Yeah.
-[Bohlale] I'm so sorry about this.

382
00:19:18.861 --> 00:19:19.861
It's not looking good.

383
00:19:24.661 --> 00:19:26.621
How are you. baby girl? How's your heart?

384
00:19:26.701 --> 00:19:29.661
After watching
what just transpired with Kuda.

385
00:19:29.741 --> 00:19:32.061
like. I'm really worried
that whatever I did

386
00:19:32.141 --> 00:19:34.061
can cause the same pain to my partner.

387
00:19:34.781 --> 00:19:36.341
-Are you ready?
-Yeah.

388
00:19:36.421 --> 00:19:38.741
-Okay. let's rip off the Band-Aid.
-Yes. let's just do it.

389
00:19:38.821 --> 00:19:40.221
-[Minnie] Let's go.
-[giggles]

390
00:19:41.021 --> 00:19:44.741
If there's one thing. I feel like.
I really appreciate about you.

391
00:19:44.821 --> 00:19:46.261
is that. like. you're a man.

392
00:19:46.861 --> 00:19:48.221
It just reminds me of what I'm lacking

393
00:19:48.301 --> 00:19:50.021
-in my relationship with my partner.
-Yoh.

394
00:19:50.101 --> 00:19:51.621
-Damn.
-[Munaka] And it's like…

395
00:19:52.861 --> 00:19:54.541
Are you in love with Gontse?

396
00:19:54.621 --> 00:19:55.621
No.

397
00:19:57.061 --> 00:19:59.141
[Gontse]
I can only grow and change so much

398
00:19:59.221 --> 00:20:01.421
till the point that
she just wants a different person.

399
00:20:01.501 --> 00:20:03.141
I just wasn't the person for you.

400
00:20:03.221 --> 00:20:04.381
Yoh.

401
00:20:04.461 --> 00:20:05.461
What?

402
00:20:05.541 --> 00:20:08.021
A part of me thinks
maybe I just chose wrong.

403
00:20:08.101 --> 00:20:11.021
So I think I also did this to myself.
you know?

404
00:20:11.101 --> 00:20:16.461
I chose someone who wouldn't love me
because that's what I feel like I deserve.

405
00:20:18.421 --> 00:20:20.021
Munaka. what do you need from him?

406
00:20:21.061 --> 00:20:22.381
I just need him to

407
00:20:23.861 --> 00:20:25.581
just be open.

408
00:20:25.661 --> 00:20:27.741
I can't connect with a rock.
I need a human.

409
00:20:28.261 --> 00:20:30.101
Be vulnerable. Make me feel wanted.

410
00:20:30.181 --> 00:20:32.261
I don't wanna feel
like you're not afraid to hurt me.

411
00:20:32.341 --> 00:20:34.381
And be committed to us as a couple.

412
00:20:34.461 --> 00:20:35.621
That's all I want.

413
00:20:35.701 --> 00:20:38.221
Everything else is perfect.
but that's what I need from him.

414
00:20:38.741 --> 00:20:42.901
And after this. I don't know if he's gonna
even want to try to do that with me.

415
00:20:42.981 --> 00:20:44.861
People fall in and out of love
all the time.

416
00:20:44.941 --> 00:20:46.701
I'm not in love right now.

417
00:20:46.781 --> 00:20:48.981
but I'm here to fall in love
with my partner again.

418
00:20:49.061 --> 00:20:50.821
Guys. I hurt that man. [groans]

419
00:20:50.901 --> 00:20:53.421
-Yeah. No. he's hurt. dawg.
-Don't say that!

420
00:20:56.541 --> 00:20:57.861
Hi. Naledi.

421
00:20:57.941 --> 00:20:58.781
Hi. How are you?

422
00:20:58.861 --> 00:21:00.221
I'm good. but how's your heart?

423
00:21:00.301 --> 00:21:03.221
The last thing I want is for my person

424
00:21:03.301 --> 00:21:06.861
to feel any ounce of pain.
any ounce of hurt.

425
00:21:06.941 --> 00:21:08.261
You ready to see?

426
00:21:08.341 --> 00:21:10.181
As ready as I'll ever be. [laughs]

427
00:21:10.261 --> 00:21:11.541
Let's watch.

428
00:21:13.501 --> 00:21:16.661
"Do you want to be
exclusively monogamous with Nikiwe?"

429
00:21:16.741 --> 00:21:17.701
No.

430
00:21:17.781 --> 00:21:20.021
That person is not polyamorous.

431
00:21:20.101 --> 00:21:23.101
They're polygamous
because they want more than one partner.

432
00:21:23.181 --> 00:21:25.021
but did not want me to have
another partner.

433
00:21:25.101 --> 00:21:26.861
That's crazy to me.

434
00:21:26.941 --> 00:21:29.381
You need to be able to buy yourself
a pair of shoes.

435
00:21:29.461 --> 00:21:31.701
To take your kid on a fucking trip.

436
00:21:31.781 --> 00:21:33.621
-[Clayton] Yeah.
-Why can't you do that?

437
00:21:33.701 --> 00:21:36.261
Why do you think you can say
stuff like this to other people?

438
00:21:36.341 --> 00:21:37.821
You don't know these people.

439
00:21:37.901 --> 00:21:39.301
What are you doing?

440
00:21:39.381 --> 00:21:40.421
What are you on?

441
00:21:40.501 --> 00:21:41.861
Yoh. Naledi wants to fight.

442
00:21:41.941 --> 00:21:43.581
-That's right.
-How do you bring up my kid?

443
00:21:43.661 --> 00:21:46.741
In that moment. do you know
how close I was to taking off my ring?

444
00:21:47.261 --> 00:21:48.341
This close.

445
00:21:50.781 --> 00:21:51.781
Careless.

446
00:21:53.981 --> 00:21:56.501
There's no context
that can make that right.

447
00:21:56.581 --> 00:21:59.381
So. I'm not even gonna try.
like. rationalize.

448
00:21:59.461 --> 00:22:01.941
I feel incredibly guilty.

449
00:22:02.621 --> 00:22:06.061
Not being able to. like. be
in a room right now with Nikiwe

450
00:22:06.141 --> 00:22:07.741
and say. "Yoh. dude. I fucked up.

451
00:22:07.821 --> 00:22:09.221
I am so sorry."

452
00:22:14.901 --> 00:22:16.101
Hello. Siya.

453
00:22:16.181 --> 00:22:17.181
Hi. ma'am.

454
00:22:18.301 --> 00:22:19.181
How are you doing?

455
00:22:19.261 --> 00:22:20.101
I'm nervous.

456
00:22:20.701 --> 00:22:23.061
-Deep breaths. You ready?
-Yeah.

457
00:22:23.141 --> 00:22:24.901
-Let's take a look.
-Okay.

458
00:22:26.381 --> 00:22:29.421
Do you feel emasculated by Pretty?

459
00:22:29.941 --> 00:22:31.021
Yes.

460
00:22:31.101 --> 00:22:34.261
At this point. I feel like
Siya doesn't have a backbone. you know.

461
00:22:34.341 --> 00:22:37.941
He's just basically listening
to what everybody is saying.

462
00:22:38.021 --> 00:22:39.941
[participants shriek. cheer]

463
00:22:41.741 --> 00:22:43.941
I'm so disappointed
that he lied to my face

464
00:22:44.021 --> 00:22:46.381
and told me that he would
never cheat on me. [sniffles]

465
00:22:46.461 --> 00:22:48.661
[all] He didn't cheat on you!

466
00:22:48.741 --> 00:22:50.781
I don't think I'll ever forgive Siya
for this. [chuckles]

467
00:22:50.861 --> 00:22:53.541
I saw a person who is just selfish. [sobs]

468
00:22:53.621 --> 00:22:55.941
And they're just thinking
about themselves.

469
00:22:56.021 --> 00:22:57.981
You don't even have a plate. boy.

470
00:22:58.061 --> 00:22:59.581
You don't even have nothing.

471
00:23:00.181 --> 00:23:01.661
You just have a suitcase.

472
00:23:02.181 --> 00:23:04.021
-She doesn't respect him.
-She's emasculating.

473
00:23:04.101 --> 00:23:06.941
-She's emasculating as fuck.
-Why do you say. "You don't have a plate?"

474
00:23:07.021 --> 00:23:08.861
It's emasculating.
whether you like it or not.

475
00:23:11.661 --> 00:23:13.061
How did that make you feel?

476
00:23:14.261 --> 00:23:16.541
To be honest. Minnie.
I don't know what to say to you. ma'am.

477
00:23:16.621 --> 00:23:20.701
I just got too comfortable with Mallay.
[in Zulu] You get me?

478
00:23:20.781 --> 00:23:22.541
[in English]
But that didn't mean anything.

479
00:23:22.621 --> 00:23:26.341
But you also need to remember
that what she saw and heard

480
00:23:26.421 --> 00:23:28.581
are things that you said and did.

481
00:23:30.701 --> 00:23:32.621
[in Sotho] Yoh. I'm speechless.

482
00:23:33.981 --> 00:23:36.821
[in English]
My time with Mallay was just great.

483
00:23:36.901 --> 00:23:41.021
And that Siya that was out there

484
00:23:41.701 --> 00:23:44.461
is the Siya that Pretty
fell in love at first.

485
00:23:44.541 --> 00:23:47.221
[in Sotho]
I'm not saying you are no good for me.

486
00:23:47.301 --> 00:23:49.461
[in English]
